==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fibrinogen
<hw>Fi*brin"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Fibrin</ets> + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>An albuminous substance existing in the blood, and in
other animal fluids, which either alone or with fibrinoplastin or
paraglobulin forms fibrin, and thus causes coagulation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fibrinogenous</ent>⟦br⟧
